	   <tr><td colspan=2>Medding on the roof is a BAD idea.<br><br>As I was medding on the roof, High Shaman Grinok (or whatever) aggro'd on me.&nbsp;&nbsp;As a 23 mage, he was yellow.  He cast malise on me, then nuked me for about 140.  I made Jabober attack, but he kept casting on me.  Since I was rooted on the roof, I kept casting my highest shock spell, and eventually killed him.<br><br>I was down to 1 bub health and 1/2 bub mana afterwards, so the resulting downtime really sucked.<br><br>Moral of this story:  If you are going to med on the roof, use your F9 views to keep an eye out for trouble.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
