	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Jan 30th 10:03 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've tanned this guy's butt for a couple of levels now (pal from levs 23 to 25).&nbsp;&nbsp;Easy Exp for sure - don't agree about comments below saying that the loot is good, he has a fine steel sword about 1 time in 10, and the rest of the time you normally get a few gold or silver (occassionally a pp or two).  But it is easy and safe levelling, if a little boring, and perhaps outside the spirit of the game.  I like to beat him up during the night, and hunt the birds during the day (don't like hunting outside at night much, and his house is always lit). A couple of tips:<br><br>- The wandering gnolls are no problem at all as long as you stay away from the outside wall, and hug the house.  I've heard them many times, but if they can't reach from outside the wall they wander off.<br><br>- It is useful to catch him before he casts his shield.  3 mins after he last died, wait in the corner on the left side of the chimney, tight in as you can and facing the house, and sit and stand repeatedly.  That way you can see clearly inside the house, and catch him with a &quot;/targ e_herm&quot; and &quot;kill you&quot; as soon as he pops.  You can then wop him throught the wall, and move back at some point to pull him out.<br><br>- If you do kill him inside the house, you can use the sit/stand method to loot his corpse.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
