	   <tr><td colspan=2>OK, here's the info needed to get the hermit.&nbsp;&nbsp;I find that targeting him through the crack in the door works well, then go to the back of the house (still inside walls though) look at the chimney, and walk to the right side of it.  Get as close to the house as you can, and then attack.  He will come to you after that.  What he drops is a cracked flute (i saw two while killing him 5 times), winds of karana page 1, and then sometimes fine steel weapons (worth about 4 to 6 plat depending on you faction and charisma).  Then if you are a caster and are worried about medding, and missing him spawn back up, don't worry.  He casts a damage shield on himself right when he spawns, so you will hear when he's back.  He casts burst of fire, that was hitting me for around 15pts a time, and his DS is worthless.  He does root though, so if you are a melee fighter, and you get him low enough he will run, so this may pose a problem, meaning you wont be able to chase him while you are rooted. That is about it.  I hope this helps you all.<br><br>Culbert, Monk of the Tribunal Server<br>Order of the Dragon's Claw<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
