	   <tr><td colspan=2>the best way to kill the hermit is kiting him solo (im a druid) or with a partner (druid, mage, wiz, or chanter work well the way i see it), but you can use your own methods if you like. pulling him using the door crack technique (see above messages) is the safest way, but watch out, cause sometimes he goes from inside the house to instantly right on top of you when pulled from outside. he hits at max from 30s to 40s, depending on if he has a weap. he drops up to 2pp but usually less, and occasionally fs weaps (!) and research pages, and usually drops either or both of: cracked flute and words of karana p1, both for a bard quest. killing the him does not cause faction changes, he only babbles some crap about vengaence. he respawns 2 mins after he is killed, which is why having a partner is good. i easily used almost all of my mana each bout. get some manacrack. he may con lvl 20, but he gives really really good exp, making him one of the best hunting choices at this level.<br><br>i hope this info helps you out.<br>happy hunting - Sariladen, Druid of &lt;WSL&gt;, Morell-Thule<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
